Plan your Research with a Literature Review

Some First Considerations

  • How feasible or doable is your research question in the time given?

  • How many observations do you need?

  • Does the answer to your question have too many angles?

Structure and availability of data

Unit of Analysis Geography Time-Period Frequency
For which level do you want data? Summary or Micro? (individuals, counties, nations) Is there a geographic component to your topic? (U.S., Sub-Saharan Africa, India) Do you want a data for a specific time period? (1980-2000, 1930-1960) How often do you want measures for your variables? (every year, every ten years, monthly, quarterly)

Data Providers

Researchers Government Agencies NGOs Research Organizations
Are there people you know who are doing this kind of research? Think about government agencies - is the request for some official statistics or data that theyd be likely to collect and publish? (industry, agriculture, construction, disease, crime) Are there councils or interest organizations devoted to the topic that might collect data independently? (HIV/AIDS, drugs, civil rights) Would any specific research organizations be interested in the topic? (Pew, Roper, Gallup, NORC, NBER, World Bank, OECD)

Mind the 80/20 Rule

It is often said that 80% of data analysis is spent on the process of cleaning and preparing the data.

-Dasu and Johnson

Scraping with R and RVEST

http://statbel.fgov.be/en/statistics/figures/economy/indicators/prix_prod_con/

library(rvest)
url='http://statbel.fgov.be/en/statistics/figures/economy/indicators/prix_prod_con/'
TAB=read_html(url)%>%html_nodes('td')%>%html_text()
NAMES=read_html(url)%>%html_nodes('th')%>%html_text()
M=data.frame(matrix(TAB,ncol=5,nrow=9,byrow=T))
M=cbind(NAMES[7:15],M)
names(M)=NAMES[1:6]
M

Activity!

Research Question: What is the relationship between availability of reproductive health services and labor force participation for women in Asia?

Searching for Data

-What search features are available to you? (Keywords, facets, etc.) How well do they work?

-Are the data described in a way that is useful?

-What formats are available?

Availability

-How tidy is the data? What might you need to do to clean it?

-How accessible is the data? Can you download a .csv? Will you have to scrape? Do you need permission?
